<step>
	<id>2</id>
	<title>pfBlockerNG Components</title>
	<description>
		<![CDATA[
		<div class="col-sm-4 alert alert-warning clearfix" role="alert">CAUTION BEFORE PROCEEDING!</div>
		<div class="col-sm-11 alert-info" style="border-style: outset; border-bottom-color: #8B181B; border-right-color: #8B181B; border-width: 2px;">
			<ul>
				<li>The pfBlockerNG wizard will configure a default setup for pfBlockerNG.</li>
				<li>This default configuration is an entry level setup which is designed to assist beginners of pfBlockerNG.</li>
				<li>If you have previously configured pfBlockerNG,
					<span style="color: red;">all settings will be wiped</span> on completion of this wizard!</li>
				<li>Two components will be installed:</li>
			</ul>
			<dl class="dl-horizontal responsive">
				<dt><strong>IP</strong>:</dt>
				<dd>Firewall rules will be added to the selected Outbound interfaces to block the worst offenders.</dd>

				<dt><strong>DNSBL</strong>:</dt>
				<dd>Utilizing the DNS Resolver, ADverts and the worst known malicious domains will be blocked.</dd>
			</dl>
		</div>
		<div class="col-sm-11">
			<br />
			<p>Click&emsp;<a href="/pfblockerng/pfblockerng_general.php?wizard=skip">
                	        <span style="color: red;">Here</span></a>&emsp;to exit this Wizard!</p>
		</div>
		]]>
	</description>
	<fields>
